sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    %% Flow 1: TrustyAI Inference Monitoring (ModelMesh)
    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 1 - TrustyAI Inference Monitoring (ModelMesh)
    participant Client as External Client
    participant MM as ModelMesh<br/>InferenceService
    participant TAS as TrustyAI Service<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Storage as Storage<br/>(PVC or PostgreSQL)
    participant Prom as Prometheus

    Client->>MM: Inference Request<br/>HTTP/gRPC (varies)
    MM->>TAS: MM_PAYLOAD_PROCESSORS callback<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS (kube-rbac-proxy)
    TAS->>Storage: Store inference data<br/>File I/O or JDBC (TLS optional)
    Prom->>TAS: Scrape /q/metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP (ServiceMonitor)
    end

    %% Flow 2: TrustyAI Inference Monitoring (KServe Raw)
    rect rgb(230, 255, 240)
    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 2 - TrustyAI Inference Monitoring (KServe Raw)
    participant KServe as KServe<br/>InferenceService
    participant Logger as InferenceLogger

    Client->>KServe: Inference Request<br/>HTTP/gRPC (varies)
    KServe->>Logger: Inference payload
    Logger->>TAS: Forward payload<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    TAS->>Storage: Store inference data<br/>File I/O or JDBC
    end

    %% Flow 3: LMEvalJob Execution
    rect rgb(255, 240, 230)
    Note over User,OCI: Flow 3 - LMEvalJob Execution
    participant User as User
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant LMES as LMES Controller
    participant LMPod as LMEvalJob Pod<br/>(driver + main)
    participant LLM as Target LLM<br/>Endpoint
    participant OCI as OCI Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    User->>K8sAPI: Create LMEvalJob CR<br/>Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>LMES: CR Watch notification
    LMES->>K8sAPI: Create Pod<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Note over LMPod: Init: driver binary<br/>copied to shared volume
    LMPod->>LLM: Evaluation queries<br/>HTTP/HTTPS (API key)
    LLM-->>LMPod: Model responses
    LMES->>LMPod: Poll status (pods/exec)<br/>TLS 1.2+ SA Token
    LMPod->>OCI: Upload results (optional)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS Registry creds
    LMPod-->>LMES: Job complete
    LMES->>K8sAPI: Update LMEvalJob status
    end

    %% Flow 4: Guardrails Orchestrator Auto-Config
    rect rgb(240, 230, 255)
    Note over Client,Detectors: Flow 4 - Guardrails Orchestrator Auto-Config
    participant GORCH as GORCH Controller
    participant GORCHSvc as Orchestrator<br/>8432/TCP HTTPS
    participant Detectors as Detector Services<br/>HTTP/HTTPS

    GORCH->>K8sAPI: List InferenceServices<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>GORCH: Discovered services
    GORCH->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment, Service, Routes<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Client->>GORCHSvc: Request via Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS reencrypt<br/>Bearer Token (SAR)
    Note over GORCHSvc: kube-rbac-proxy → 8032/TCP
    GORCHSvc->>Detectors: Detector requests<br/>HTTP/HTTPS TLS (configurable)
    Detectors-->>GORCHSvc: Detection results
    GORCHSvc-->>Client: Guardrails response
    end

    %% Flow 5: EvalHub Multi-Tenant Evaluation
    rect rgb(255, 255, 230)
    Note over User,EvalJob: Flow 5 - EvalHub Multi-Tenant Evaluation
    participant EvalHub as EvalHub<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PgSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>TLS (optional)
    participant EvalJob as Evaluation Job Pod

    User->>EvalHub: Submit evaluation<br/>443/TCP HTTPS Route reencrypt<br/>Bearer Token (SAR)
    EvalHub->>PgSQL: Store evaluation config<br/>JDBC, Username/Password
    EvalHub->>K8sAPI: Create Job in tenant NS<br/>Job ServiceAccount
    K8sAPI-->>EvalJob: Pod scheduled
    EvalJob->>LLM: Evaluation queries<br/>HTTP/HTTPS (varies)
    LLM-->>EvalJob: Results
    EvalJob-->>EvalHub: Job complete
    EvalHub->>PgSQL: Store results
    end
